  "prompt": "Personal Productivity: Is there a service that allows bookmarking of quotes?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several services and tools that allow you to bookmark and save quotes for personal productivity and inspiration. Here are a few:\n\n1. **Evernote**: This versatile note-taking app allows you to save quotes along with other types of notes. You can organize quotes into notebooks, tag them, and easily search for them later.\n\n2. **Pocket**: Originally designed for saving articles to read later, Pocket can also be used to save quotes and other snippets of text. You can tag saved items for easy retrieval.\n\n3. **Notion**: Notion is a powerful organizational tool that lets you create databases, notes, and pages. You can create a dedicated page or database for quotes, categorizing and tagging them as you wish.\n\n4. **Readwise**: Readwise is specifically designed for highlighting and saving quotes from ebooks and articles. It can sync with services like Kindle, Instapaper, and Pocket to aggregate your favorite quotes and even send you daily reminders to review them.\n\n5. **Google Keep**: Google Keep is a simple note-taking app that syncs across devices. You can easily save quotes and organize them using labels.\n\n6. **Quotebook**: Quotebook is an app designed specifically for saving quotes. It lets you organize quotes by author, source, and tags, providing an easy way to review and share them.\n\n7. **Diigo**: Diigo is a social bookmarking tool that allows users to save, organize, and annotate web pages and quotes. It provides robust features for tagging and categorization.\n\nEach of these tools offers unique features that cater to different needs, so you can choose the one that fits best with your workflow and organizational style.\n",
